window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>Because You Loved Me: I Don t Mind Falling In Love, All Over Again</i> presents the story of a young boy as he does everything that's possible to win back the heart of his lady love, Aarushi. The story is set in 2009, in urban India, and the protagonist is Ritesh Garg, who, like all the other Class X students, is about to appear for his all-important final exams in a few days. But for Ritesh, exam preparations are relegated to the back burner as he is on a single-minded mission to get the love of his life - a girl named Aarushi - back into his life. Ritesh s feelings are out there for all to see, but Aarushi s feelings for Ritesh are unknown. Also, her brother Aryan is caught between wanting Ritesh to suffer and wanting Aarushi to be happy. Meanwhile, Aarushi s mother wants her to focus solely on the board exams and perform extremely well in them. Some of the other characters in the story are Pallu, Shreelekha, Gupta, and Laharry - each of them in pursuit of a different goal. </p><p>As the story progresses, Ritesh meets one obstacle after another, and his journey is toughened by the conflicting desires of the other characters in the story. From frightening accidents to cash-flow problems, Ritesh must overcome numerous challenges if he wants to regain Aarushi's love, which seems like a tall order. </p>"; 
